race.comment: LAVA LAD (3) is in white-hot form. Was successful last start over this track and trip getting home by half a length to make it four wins on the bounce. Doing everything right at the moment and there's no reason he can't score again. GEORGIEGINA (11) has returned in great order, with two barnstorming victories at long odds. Has to be respected now, despite the ugly draw. OVERSTRIKE (2) has switched yards since finishing seventh two-and-a-half weeks ago over 1200m at Gawler. Made a mess of his rivals fresh in this grade and is a big danger if he can recapture that form. THE WIRRULLA BOY (5) was well in the market again when third at this track and starting to prove costly but does tend to run well here. Going well without winning so don't underestimate.
